  {
    question: "How is deep cleaning different from regular cleaning?",
    answer: "Regular cleaning focuses on keeping your home fresh and tidy week to week—dusting surfaces, vacuuming/mopping floors, sanitizing kitchens and bathrooms, and maintaining high-traffic areas.\n\nDeep cleaning, on the other hand, goes much further. It targets built-up dirt, grime, and hidden areas that don’t get as much attention during routine cleanings. This includes:\n• Scrubbing baseboards, vents, blinds, and fixtures\n• Cleaning inside cabinets, appliances, and other detailed areas\n• Removing deep buildup in kitchens, bathrooms, and hard-to-reach spaces\n\nIn short, regular cleaning maintains your home, while deep cleaning resets it—leaving every corner spotless and refreshed."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does a deep cleaning take?",
    answer: "The time needed for a deep cleaning depends on the size of your home, its condition, and the level of detail required. On average, most deep cleanings take anywhere from 4 to 8 hours. Larger homes or those with heavier buildup may require additional time.\n\nDuring your free consultation, we’ll walk through your home, discuss your priorities, and provide a clear time estimate so you know exactly what to expect."
  },
  {
    question: "Do I need to prepare anything before the deep cleaning?",
    answer: "Preparation isn’t mandatory, but a few quick steps help us focus time on detailed cleaning:\n\n• Tidy surfaces & floors: Pick up toys, clothes, and personal items so we can clean every surface thoroughly.\n• Secure pets: Keep pets in a safe area or outside the work zones for their comfort and our team’s safety.\n• Access & instructions: Provide entry details, alarm codes, and any special notes (delicate items, rooms to skip, priorities).\n• Fragile & valuables: Please move or clearly mark fragile/heirloom items you’d prefer we don’t handle.\n• Parking & water/electric: Ensure convenient parking and access to water and power.\n• Linens & beds (optional): Leave fresh sheets out if you’d like us to change them.\n• Inside-appliance cleaning (optional): If you’ve added oven or refrigerator interior cleaning, please remove contents beforehand.\n\nWe’ll also review your priorities at the start of the visit so the team focuses on what matters most to you."
  },
  {
    question: "How often should I schedule a deep cleaning? And why?",
    answer: "Most homes benefit from a deep cleaning every 3 to 6 months. This frequency helps prevent buildup in kitchens, bathrooms, and hard-to-reach areas while keeping your home healthier and easier to maintain with regular cleanings in between.\n\nYou may want to schedule deep cleaning more often if:\n• You have children, pets, or frequent guests.\n• You host special events and want your home at its best.\n• You notice dust, grime, or buildup in places not covered during routine cleaning.\n\nRegular deep cleaning not only improves your home’s appearance but also extends the life of surfaces, appliances, and finishes—protecting your investment and ensuring a consistently fresh environment."
  }
];



